refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public boolImagick::rotateImage mixedbackground floatdegrees
Rotates an image the specified number of degrees. Empty triangles left over from rotating the image are filled with the background color.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     PECL imagick 2.1.0

      Now allows a string representing the color as the first parameter.
      Previous versions allow only an ImagickPixel object.

  &reftitle.examples;



       Imagick::rotateImage


<?php
function rotateImage($imagePath, $angle, $color) {
    $imagick = new \Imagick(realpath($imagePath));
    $imagick->rotateimage($color, $angle);
    header("Content-Type: image/jpg");
    echo $imagick->getImageBlob();
}

?>
